Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Peel and finely dice @carrots{4}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim, then roughly chop @button mushrooms{4%oz}. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%oz}. Remove @sweet Italian pork sausage{18%oz} from casings.

Heat @olive oil{4%tsp} in a large pan over medium heat. Add onion, carrots, and garlic and cook until softened, about ~{5%minutes}. Toss in mushrooms and cook until tender, about ~{5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{12%oz} to pot. Cook until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Once mushrooms are tender, add sausage to pan, breaking up meat into pieces. Cook until no longer pink, about ~{5%minutes}.

Stir @crushed tomatoes{2%14oz boxes}, pasta cooking water, and @chicken stock concentrate{1} into pan. Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir @spinach{10%oz} into pan with Bolognese and let wilt.

> TIP: If Bolognese is not saucy or seems stiff, add an extra splash of water.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide spaghetti between plates and top with Bolognese. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/2%cup} and parsley.